<inglise> /* Commission Regulation No 474/67/EEC of 21 August 1967 on the advance fixing of the export refund on rice and broken rice </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS nr 474/67/EM&Uuml; riisi ja purustatud riisi eksporditoetuse eelneva kinnitamise kohta 21. august 1967 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation N&egrave; 359/67/EEC of 25 July 1967 on the common organization of the market in rice (1), and in particular Article 17 (6) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 25. juuli 1967. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust nr 359/67/EM&Uuml; riisituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) eriti selle artikli 17 l&otilde;iget 6, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 17 of the abovementioned Regulation provides that for exports of rice and broken rice the difference between quotations or prices on the world market and prices within the Community may be covered by an export refund which may be fixed in advance; whereas, in the case of advance fixing, the refund must be adjusted for the threshold price which will be in force during the month in which export takes place and a corrective amount, fixed at the same time, must be applied to the refund; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: eespool nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 17 n&auml;hakse ette, et riisi ja purustatud riisi ekspordi puhul v&otilde;ib noteeringute v&otilde;i maailmaturuhindade ja &uuml;henduse hindade vahe katta eksporditoetusega, mille v&otilde;ib eelnevalt kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata; eelneva kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramise puhul tuleb toetust kohandada ekspordikuul kehtiva k&uuml;nnishinna alusel ja toetuse suhtes tuleb kohaldada samal ajal kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud korrigeerivat summat; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to assess the amount of the refund to be granted when this is fixed in advance, the variation in world market prices which may occur between the day on which the application for the licence is made and the month in which exportation takes place has to be estimated; whereas the cif forward delivery price reflects this variation and thus enables the amount by which the refund valid on the day on which the application for the licence is made to be reduced or increased; </inglise>
<eesti> antava toetuse summa hindamiseks toetuse eelneva kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramise korral tuleb hinnata maailmaturuhindade k&otilde;ikumist, mis v&otilde;ivad ilmneda litsentsi taotlemise p&auml;eva ja eksportimiskuu vahel; t&auml;htajaline CIF-tarnehind peegeldab seda k&otilde;ikumist ja v&otilde;imaldab seega arvutada v&auml;lja summa, mille v&otilde;rra v&auml;hendatakse v&otilde;i suurendatakse litsentsitaotluse esitamise p&auml;eval kehtivat eksporditoetust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it would be inadvisable for the amount of refunds to vary too frequently as a result of minimal changes in world market quotations, thus causing uncertainty for those entitled to them; whereas, therefore, without harming the interests of those entitled, a limit should be set within which variations in these quotations do not affect the amount of the refund; </inglise>
<eesti> toetusesummde liiga sagedane k&otilde;ikumine maailmaturu noteeringute v&auml;ikeste muutuste tulemusel oleks ebasoovitav, kuna see p&otilde;hjustaks ebakindlust nende jaoks, kellel on &otilde;igus toetust saada; selleks, et mitte kahjustada v&otilde;imalike toetuse saajate huve, tuleks s&auml;testada piirid, mille ulatuses noteeringute k&otilde;ikumised ei m&otilde;juta toetuse summat; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Cereals, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las teraviljaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Where the export refund on rice and broken rice referred to in the first subparagraph of Article 17 (4) of Regulation N&egrave; 359/67/EEC is fixed in advance, the refund shall be that which is applicable to an export on the day on which the licence is applied for: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse nr 359/67/EM&Uuml; artikli 17 l&otilde;ike 4 esimeses l&otilde;igus osutatud riisi ja purustatud riisi eksporditoetuse eelneva kinnitamise korral on toetus see, mida kohaldatakse ekspordi suhtes litsentsi taotlemise p&auml;eval ja mida: </eesti>
<inglise> - reduced by the difference between the cif forward delivery price and the cif price where the former exceeds the latter by more than 0.025 unit of account per 100 kilogrammes; </inglise>
<eesti> - on v&auml;hendatud t&auml;htajalise CIF-tarnehinna ja CIF-hinna vahe v&otilde;rra juhul, kui esimene &uuml;letab viimast rohkem kui 0.025 arvestus&uuml;hikut 100 kilogrammi kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> - increased by the difference between the cif price and the cif forward delivery price where the former exceeds the latter by more than 0.025 unit of account per 100 kilogrammes. </inglise>
<eesti> - suurendatakse CIF-hinna ja t&auml;htajalise CIF-tarnehinna vahe v&otilde;rra juhul, kui esimene &uuml;letab viimast rohkem kui 0.025 arvestus&uuml;hikut 100 kilogrammi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> In the intervals between weekly fixings, the amount of the refund applicable in the case of advance fixing shall be adjusted when application of the above method of calculation would lead to its amount being altered by more than 0.025 unit of account per 100 kilogrammes. </inglise>
<eesti> Igan&auml;dalaste kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiste vahelisel ajal kohandatakse eelneva kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramise puhul kohaldatavat toetuse summat siis, kui eespool nimetatud arvestusmeetod tooks kaasa toetuse summa muutumise rohkem kui 0.025 arvestus&uuml;hiku v&otilde;rra 100 kilogrammi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> The cif price for this purpose shall be that calculated in accordance with Article 16 of Regulation N&egrave; 359/67/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel eesm&auml;rgil arvutatakse CIF-hind vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 359/67/EM&Uuml; artiklile 16. </eesti>
<inglise> The cif forward delivery price shall be that calculated in accordance with Article 3 (2) of Regulation N&egrave; 365/67/EEC (2) based, however, in respect of each (1) OJ N&egrave; 174, 31.7.1967, p. 1. (2) OJ N&egrave; 174, 31.7.1967, p. 32. month for which the export licence is valid, on the cif price calculated on the basis of offers for shipment during the month in which export will be effected. </inglise>
<eesti> T&auml;htajaline CIF-tarnehind on vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 365/67/EM&Uuml; (2) artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele 2 arvutatud hind, mis p&otilde;hineb ekspordilitsentsi iga kehtimiskuu puhul CIF-hinnal, mis on arvutatud ekspordikuu jooksul tehtud veopakkumiste p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on 1 September 1967. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 1. septembril 1967. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 21 August 1967. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 21. august 1967 Komisjoni nimel </eesti>
